<h2 id="who-its-for">👥 Who Should Automate Med Spa Lead Follow-Up?</h2>

**This is ideal for:**
- Med spas spending $3,000+/month on advertising with inconsistent follow-up
- Multi-location groups struggling with centralized intake
- Solo practitioners who can't be tethered to their phone
- High-volume practices doing 50+ consultations monthly
- Owners planning to scale beyond their current location count

**This might not be right for:**
- Brand-new med spas still refining their service offerings
- Ultra-luxury practices where white-glove human touch is the product
- Operators unwilling to invest 20+ hours in initial setup
- Practices with fewer than 20 leads/month (manual follow-up is fine at low volume)

The break-even point typically hits around 30-40 leads per month. Below that threshold, a well-trained front desk person can handle follow-up effectively. Above it, humans become the bottleneck and automation ROI turns positive quickly.

